data.title: En Route Label Art From The Golden Age of Air Travel
data.meta_description:
En Route Label Art From the Golden Age of Air Travel - Read online for free. Enroute features over 125 beautiful luggage labels 
produced by the early commercial airlines of the United States, 
Europe, Canada, and Latin America. From the complex, almost 
Edwardian, designs of the earliest flying days and the bold style 
of the Art Deco period, to the modern icons of the forties and 
fifties, these spectacular labels reflect the convergence of art, 
design, and technology within the context of aviation history.
